{"id": "06396d9e20b74e669872998d3c486c5c", "timestamp": "2025-12-10 23:18:22", "name": "Scientist0", "content": "Thought: The historical dialogue reveals a clear convergence on the limitations of current GNN-based models in capturing the dual dynamics of emotional evolution and relational change in multi-party dialogues. Recurring themes include the need for dynamic graph updates, sensitivity to temporal affective patterns (emotional hysteresis), and adaptability to structural shifts (relational plasticity). The proposed hybrid mechanism—combining continuous-time message passing with event-driven topology updates—represents an innovative integration of neural and symbolic insights that directly addresses these gaps. This approach not only advances modeling fidelity but also opens new avenues for interpretable, temporally aware dialogue systems. The two-tier evaluation strategy strengthens its scientific rigor, while applications in mental health and social AI underscore its potential impact. Given its originality, technical grounding, and relevance to high-stakes domains, this topic is both timely and transformative.\n\nTopic: ```json{\"Selected Topic\": \"A Hybrid Graph Update Mechanism for Jointly Modeling Emotional Hysteresis and Relational Plasticity in Multi-Party Dialogues\"}```", "role": "assistant", "url": null, "metadata": null, "_colored_name": "\u001b[91mScientist0\u001b[0m"}
{"id": "2dbb69e4b3bd40a7b065c4fb674f85f7", "timestamp": "2025-12-10 23:18:26", "name": "Scientist0", "content": "The selected topic focuses on developing a hybrid graph update mechanism to jointly model emotional hysteresis and relational plasticity in multi-party dialogues using the TEDiG framework. The approach integrates continuous-time message passing for emotional dynamics and event-driven updates for relational changes, offering improved modeling fidelity and interpretability. A two-tier evaluation with synthetic and real-world datasets will validate both mechanism accuracy and practical utility. This work is deemed original, technically sound, and impactful for applications in mental health and social AI, warranting immediate progression to experiment design and prototyping.", "role": "assistant", "url": null, "metadata": null, "_colored_name": "\u001b[91mScientist0\u001b[0m"}
